Tier 1: Foundational
Product Enhancements**
1. Integrate a Persistent Database: Switch from temporary Redis storage to a robust database (like PostgreSQL) for storing user data and saved itineraries. This is a prerequisite for user accounts. //COMPLETE
2. Implement User Accounts & Profiles: Add user registration, login, and a profile section to save travel preferences (e.g., "Foodie," "Art Lover").  //COMPLETE
3. Integrate Live Data API: Replace static JSON files with a live data source like the Google Places API to get real-time ratings, hours, and photos.  //COMPLETE
4. Develop Interactive Itinerary Editing: Allow users to drag-and-drop activities, remove spots, and regenerate parts of their plan. //COMPLETE

Tier 2: Monetization & Commercialization

Implement Freemium "Pro" Tier: Create a subscription model that unlocks advanced features like multi-city planning and PDF export.
Integrate Affiliate & Booking APIs: Add "Book Now" buttons for hotels (Booking.com), activities (Viator), and restaurants (OpenTable) to generate commission.
Tier 3: Scalability & Technical Excellence

Set up Analytics & Business Intelligence: Integrate an analytics tool to track user behavior and guide product decisions.
Build CI/CD Pipeline: Use GitHub Actions to automate testing and deployment, ensuring code quality and faster releases.
